title: Bug Therapy
des: Citronella, a mosquito who faints at the sight of blood, waits nervously outside her first group-therapy session, while the therapist, "Dr. Pill" tries to calm a rambunctious group of bugs -- each suffering from their own psychological problem. A germaphobic Fly freaks out when he runs out of hand sanitizer. A clingy female Dragonfly struggles to give her boyfriend the "space" he needs (she's literally on top of him). A jumpy Grasshopper, addicted to coffee, launches himself in mid-sentence. A confused Praying Mantis anguishes over his doubt about God. A terrified Spider searches the area, because he's deathly afraid of --spiders. And, a well-hidden Stickbug complains that no one ever "sees" him. Throughout this wait, Citronella battles her urge to flee - until Dr. Pill finally asks her to introduce herself - and share her "embarrassing" problem.
